                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/18469</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Garrett</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Laredo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-06-17T17:00:00-06:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 17, 1916, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Three American soldiers were killed and six wounded and eight Mexicans killed in
                    battle at San Ygnacio on fifteenth instant. Another expedition is being
                    organized, of which Colonel George Guiterrez will be commander and Major Pedro
                    Vena second in command. It is planned to make it larger than the last invading
                    party and it will probably cross or attempt to cross in same region.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Garrett</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
